Can we change the two layer for loop to one like:
```suggestion
    for (Message *message = queues[index]->GetHead(); message && message->GetPriority() < aPriority; message = message->GetNext())
    {
        if (message->GetDoNotEvict())
        {
            continue;
        }
```
I checked some code of `PriorityQueue`:
```
Message *PriorityQueue::GetHeadForPriority(uint8_t aPriority) const
{
    Message *head;
    Message *previousTail;

    if (mTails[aPriority] != NULL)
    {
        previousTail = FindFirstNonNullTail(PrevPriority(aPriority));

        OT_ASSERT(previousTail != NULL);

        head = previousTail->Next();
    }
    else
    {
        head = NULL;
    }

    return head;
}
```
So it seems that the tail of one priority links to the head of next priority. Then I think we can traverse it from low priority to high priority in this way, a little simpler.

