Some states are still unavailable here. E..g, `node_manager_port` is 0 here, and will be set when the node manager grpc server starts (in the constructor of node manger). 
That's why we get these attributes and send to GCS in `Raylet::RegisterGcs`. I think we can also delay initializing `gcs_client` until `RegisterGcs`, or make `ClientTableData` as a parameter of `Connect`.  E.g., 

```
/// Connect to the GCS. This method is used by non-raylet GcsClient. 
Status Connect();

/// Connect to the GCS and register ourself as a new node of the cluster.
/// This method is used by raylet.
Status ConnectAndRegisterNode(ClientTableData data);
```

By doing this, we can get rid of `ClientInfo`. And it's very clear that `ClientTableData` is only used by raylet.

Btw, I'd like to rename `ClientTableData` to `NodeInfo`. Because the name is very ambiguous.

